  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "After the success of the Salvation's Reach raid, the Tanith First races to the strategically vital forge world of Urdesh, where the Sabbat Crusade has converged for a decisive open-ground battle against Anarch Sek's massed armies. Warmaster Macaroth himself commands the Urdesh campaign from a field headquarters at Eltath, and the Archenemy push — Blood Pact infantry led by the elite Sons of Sek — may be aimed not at the planet but at the Warmaster's person, a single-blow attempt to decapitate the entire Crusade command structure. Gaunt, now serving on Macaroth's personal staff, threads regimental command of the Tanith with brokered relationships across the Crusade's senior generals — Cybon, Van Voytz, Kelso, Bulledin, Lugo, Blackwood. The novel runs as a forge-world siege-and-counter-siege procedural, with the regiment's Felyx-Chass subplot deepening and the Sek faction emerging as the dominant Archenemy presence. Closes mid-campaign on Urdesh, with The Anarch continuing the assault on Eltath.",
